New Records: Gunnar Henderson tied the Baltimore Orioles single-season shortstop home run record with 34 homers.
Key Match Events: Gunnar Henderson hit a leadoff home run in the first inning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles scored 13 runs in the game, with each starter recording a hit and scoring a run for the first time since Aug. 25, 2017.
Others: The game was played at Camden Yards against the Chicago White Sox, helping the Orioles maintain pace at a half game behind the Yankees at the top of the AL East standings.
